hermit-at (1.1.0) stable; urgency=low

  * This is a pretty big change since the last one; here goes:
  * Big flash code refactor and generalization.  we now have a generic flash
    layer on top of each type of flash (NOR and SPI)
  * added support for all flash types in gunzip
  * new type system (ie: u8, u16, u32)
  * new compiler support for microblaze (v3.4.1)
  * added new io accessors
  * remove windows new line code
  * added new --baudrate option
  * suzaku: trun the red led on when in hmain()
  * added a version string (ie, "v1.1.0") to the target binary files
  * many bug fixes

 -- Masahiro Nakai <nakai@atmark-techno.com>  Thu, 13 Jul 2006 02:57:00 +0900

